Class Action

java.lang.Object
  org.gwt.mosaic.actions.client.Action
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.google.gwt.user.client.Command, com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.ClickListener, com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.HasText, java.util.EventListener
public class Action
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.google.gwt.user.client.Command, com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.HasText, com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.ClickListener

An action represents the non-UI side of a command which can be triggered by the end user. Actions are typically associated with buttons, menu items, and items in tool bars. When the end user triggers the command via its control, the action's execute method is invoked to do the real work.
